summary: An Ordinance appropriating the sum of One Hundred Fifty ($150.) Dollars from the general fund of the City of Seattle to pay the claim of A. F. Dively and Amelia A. Dively, his wife, for personal injuries received by said Amelia A. Dively on September 1, 1914, at about ten o'clock A. M., while walking along and upon the sidewalk upon the north side of Roxbury Street, Seattle, Washington, about half way between Fifty-sixth and Fifty-seventh Avenue South, in the City of Seattle, Washington, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
